      • add

        public void add(T x)
         throws ADTExceptions
        Adds an element to the orderedlist. First determines if the list is empty. Then determines if it's a duplicate. From there, it determines if the element is to go at the front of the list. After that it determines where the element should go within the list.
        Parameters:
        x - the element the user attempts to add.
        Throws:
        ADTExceptions - upon attempted addition of an element which would violate uniqueness.
